# Engineering Journal for 18mm Model Rocket Display Stand

## Problem

My model rockets are really precious to me, and the 18mm ones are one of my best performing ones. Unfortunately, they don't have a proper position in which i can set them down without incurring damage. Due to this, 3 of my rockets now have broken fins and are unable to be re-used. This provided me with an idea to design a stand for them which keeps them presentable and usable while using them as a mantle-piece.

## Step 1: Fabricate V1 (37 mins)

I began designing V1, which used an arch as the base support around a central 18mm rod on which the rocket would be placed. The design was very unappealling and looked like a bulky paperweight, not the sleek minimalist look i was aiming for. The curvature of the design also allowed it to easily roll over, destroying the rocket.

## Step 2: Redesign the stand for stability (1 hr 46 mins)

I redesigned the part with minimalism in mind, and, for structural intergrity and balance, used a triangular shaped design. A hexagonal shaped base pattern was used for a more appealing finish and to decrease the amount of material used. V2 had a steeper incline for the rocket's position, which provided more stablity for taller rockets. The wider and larger base area also adds more stability to the design, making it perfect for my use. 

## Step 3: Design an additional stand as a challenge (57 mins)

As a challenge, i decided to take a completely different approach to the design, modelling a unique design that allows the rocket to look like its floating, with an extremely small base to support it. The stand was designed to seem invisible, and be something easily forgotten. Unfortunately the new design lacked structure and support, collapsing instantly under weight. Additionally, the design had a small base, decreasing the stability of the design and making it easy to tip over. Thus, i decided that V2 was best suited to my requirements.


## Step 4: Complete project and Write README + JOURNAL (1 hr 18 mins)

After finalising the project, i wrote a proper, detailed README and JOURNAL to upload my completed project.



